{\*\generator Msftedit 5.41.15.1515;}\viewkind4\uc1\pard\cf1\b\f0\fs20 Sometimes you will want to show an entire list of items, but you want the user positioned on one record.\par
\par
This is accomplished in Magic by using the \cf2 Locate\cf1  property. Whereas the Range property will restrict the number of records that are displayed, the Locate property just changes which record is current.\par
\par
In this example, when you change the Last initial, the table relocates to the first record with with a last name that matches the initial. If no such record is found, it positions to the closest match.\par
}
